            <title>[HBASE-6128] Use weights instead of block counts in DoubleBlockCache with CacheBuilder</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6128</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5739&quot; title=&quot;Upgrade guava to 11.0.2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5739&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5739&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we can now specify a max weight instead of a maximum number of blocks in the DoubleBlockCache. This will give a more accurate control over its memory usage.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
